  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SENIOR MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Conduct real estate market research, site investigations, and project investment assessments;</li><li>Compile market research and data collections on various real estate matters;</li><li>Collect development land & project information to perform the preliminary analysis;</li><li>Develop tender strategies and positions by studying the land tender documents, examining risks and potential opportunities;</li><li>Prepare feasibility study reports in Chinese, and liaise with HQ for clarifications and follow-ups to ensure approvals are obtained;</li><li>Prepare working papers, correspondence, documents, plans, presentation materials and other relevant materials;</li><li>Liaise with external consultants, such as marketing consultants and legal consultants;</li><li>Perform feasibility studies and evaluations of the projects, including financial, market, and economic analyses</li><li>Preparing the annual investment budget and cash flow plans, ensuring rationality and effective implementation;</li><li>Coordinate audits and compliance checks for real estate projects. Lead issue tracking and ensure timely resolution;</li><li>Any other assignment as and when required.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>A Bachelor Degree/ Master Degree in Real Estate, Business, Finance, Economics, Engineering, or other related fields;</li><li>At least 5 years of relevant experience in real estate, investment, business development, or finance and accounting, with a good understanding of the real estate sector;</li><li>Working experience in a Chinese real estate developer, especially with a finance and accounting background, will be preferred;</li><li>Familiarity with the Singapore real estate market and regulations set by relevant government authorities will be preferred;</li><li>Proficiency in spoken and written English and Mandarin;</li><li>A proven track record in investment and development projects;</li><li>Ability to manage multiple tasks and perform well under pressure;</li><li>Good knowledge of relevant software.</li></ul>",
